+ Class Methods

++ Public

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::isLoginRequest() -- Is the current page-load a login request?

We can tell because there will be certain GET params in place:

<code>
&ts=1149633028
&email=clay%40mashery.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::isLoginValid() -- Is the current login attempt valid?

The signature must pass DSA verification, and the timestamp of
the signature must be within the time-window (this is to avoid
replay attacks).

Inherited Methods:

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::__construct() -- Constructor.

* Solar_Base::apiVersion() -- Reports the API version for this class.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::getEmail() -- Returns the current user email address.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::getErrCode() -- Returns the most recent error code.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::getHandle() -- Returns the current user handle.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::getMoniker() -- Returns the current user "full name" or "display name".

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::getUri() -- Returns the current user URI.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::isLogoutRequest() -- Tells if the current page load appears to be the result of
an attempt to log out.

* Solar_Base::locale() -- Looks up locale strings based on a key.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::reset() -- Clears handle, passwd, email, moniker, and uri properties.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter::setCommon() -- Sets information for "common" handle + passwd authentication
systems.

++ Protected

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_bc_bindec() -- Converts a binary value string to a decimal value string using
bcmath functions.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_bc_exgcd() -- Finds the extended greatest-common-denominator of two values
using bcmath functions.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_bc_hexdec() -- Converts a hex value string to a decimal value string using
bcmath functions.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_bc_invert() -- Inverts two values using bcmath functions.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_fetchKeyData() -- Fetches the public key data from TypeKey.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_gmp_bindec() -- Converts a binary to a decimal value using GMP functions.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_verify() -- Verifies login using either GMP or bcmath functions.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_verify_bc() -- DSA verification using bcmath.

* Solar_Auth_Adapter_Typekey::_verify_gmp() -- DSA verification using GMP.

Inherited Methods:

* Solar_Base::_exception() -- Convenience method for returning exceptions with localized text.

++ Private

None.